        <updateDate>2022-11-15T23:45:09Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>State, Tribal, and Local Species Transparency and Recovery Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of the Interior or the Department of Commerce, as appropriate, to provide to affected states all data that is used as the basis of a determination on whether a species is an endangered species or a threatened species before making a determination.</p> <p>The appropriate department must also use data submitted by a state, tribal, or local government in making such a determination.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
